<subSubSection id="C358B5E6FFA5F079FF67FE31FC4EFDFA" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFDE66DFFA5F079FF67FE31FC4EFDFA" blockId="19.[192,1442,408,536]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FF67FE31FEDDFE50" bold="true" box="[192,316,408,434]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The forewing pattern of 
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FDFCFE30FCA5FE50" authorityName="Phillips and Brown" authorityYear="2021" box="[603,836,408,435]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Chlamydastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernardoespinozai">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FDFCFE30FCA5FE50" box="[603,836,408,435]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">C. bernardoespinozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is somewhat irregularly checkered and unlike that of other species in this group. The male genitalia are most similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FC4CFE12FB7CFE36" authorityName="Phillips and Brown" authorityYear="2021" box="[1003,1181,442,469]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Chlamydastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bobandersoni">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FC4CFE12FB7CFE36" box="[1003,1181,442,469]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">C. bobandersoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FA88FE12FEA1FE14" authorityName="Phillips and Brown" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Chlamydastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernardoespinozai">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FA88FE12FEA1FE14" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">C. bernardoespinozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a larger, broader uncus; a less undulate lower ventral edge of the sacculus; a less pointed distal end of the sacculus; and a much longer distal sclerite of the phallus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358B5E6FFA5F079FF67FD8EFA7DFB48" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFDE66DFFA5F079FF67FD8EFDD5FC35" blockId="19.[192,1442,551,1118]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FF67FD8EFEB3FDA3" bold="true" box="[192,338,551,577]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Description.</emphasis>
MALE (
<figureCitation id="1379FAE8FFA5F079FE16FD8EFDE0FDA0" box="[433,513,551,578]" captionStart="Figures 9–15" captionStartId="15.[192,279,1765,1791]" captionTargetBox="[232,1355,300,1699]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[192,1390,213,1716]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figures 9–15. Adults of Chlamydastis from Costa Rica – Curviliniella Species Group. 9) C. anniapicadoae, holotype, male, INB0003545350. 10) C. antonioazofeifai, holotype, male, INB0003317783. 11) C. mignondavisae, holotype female, USNMENT 01480465. 12) C. marianofigueresi, paratype female, 16-SRNP-105464. 13) C. colleenhitchcockae, holotype male, 97-SRNP-1651. 14) C. bernardoespinozai, holotype, male, 09-SRNP-107481. 15) C. bobandersoni, paratype, male, INBIOCRI001138251." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042027" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042027/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FDB4FD8EFDAFFDA3" box="[531,590,551,577]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Head</emphasis>
. Frons, vertex and collar whitish; labial palpus cream with yellow and brown scales intermixed forming a lateral band along first segment and basal 0.75 of second segment; antenna with sensory setae ca. 1.5 times width of flagellomere. 
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FD49FDC2FCDAFD67" box="[750,827,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Thorax</emphasis>
. Dorsum and tegula whitish intermixed with greenish scales, pro- and metathorax with narrow greenish band. FW length 
<quantity id="4CBA4B88FFA5F079FC62FD24FBBDFD45" box="[965,1116,653,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" metricValueMax="10.5" metricValueMin="9.1" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="9.8" valueMax="10.5" valueMin="9.1">9.1–10.5 mm</quantity>
; FW ground color pale olive with traces of gray green overscaling and irregular spots and streaks of dark brown and brownish olive; three dark, ill-defined blotches along costa at ca. 0.25, 0.50, and 0.75 distance from base to apex; a short black dash through middle of discal cell ending in a small pale spot; greenish olive band from outer margin of pale spot at end of discal cell to hind margin just before tornus. 
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FCB1FCBDFC9FFCCC" box="[790,894,788,814]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Externally pale brown. Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="1379FAE8FFA5F079FAAAFCBDFABCFCCD" box="[1293,1373,788,815]" captionStart="Figures 57–64" captionStartId="50.[192,279,1732,1758]" captionTargetBox="[290,1348,244,1672]" captionTargetId="figure-87@50.[284,1348,216,1703]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Figures 57–64. Male genitalia (phallus detached) of Chlamydastis from Costa Rica – Curviliniella and Mendoron SpeciesGroups.57) C.anniapicadoae,paratype,INBIOCRI0004263586.58) C.antonioazofeifai,paratype,09-SRNP- 103461. 59) C. marianofigueresi, holotype, 16-SRNP-105662 (USNM 153,780) (phallus INBIOCRI002183316). 60) C. colleenhitchcockae, holotype, 97-SRNP-1651. 61) C. bernardoespinozai, paratype, 10-SRNP-104626. 62) C. bobandersoni, paratype, 09-SRNP-111006. 63) C. carlosviquezi, paratype, INBIOCRI000616538. 64) C. christerhanssoni, paratype, INBIOCRI000788466." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042045" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042045/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
) with uncus large, broad; anterior margin at intersection of lateral halves of tegumen forming a rounded arch; gnathos absent; dorsal part of valva ovate, evenly attenuate apically, with dense patch of specialized setae along middle of costa, irregularly triangular basal part representing sacculus ca. 0.5 length of valva, with weakly developed haripencil; lateral processes of juxta as long as their bases; two semicircular sclerotized lines laterally at base of juxta; phallus with a long distal sclerite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFDE66DFFA5F079FEA7FC76FC32FBBC" blockId="19.[192,1442,551,1118]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
FEMALE. 
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FEDCFC77FE57FC1A" box="[379,438,990,1016]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Head</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FE51FC77FDA5FC1A" box="[502,580,990,1016]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Thorax</emphasis>
. Essentially as described for male, except sensory setae of antenna short, sparse; FW length 
<quantity id="4CBA4B88FFA5F079FE35FBA9FDD7FBF9" box="[402,566,1024,1051]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.135" metricValueMax="1.16" metricValueMin="1.1099999999999999" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="11.35" valueMax="11.6" valueMin="11.1">11.1–11.6 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FDE6FBA9FD4BFBF8" box="[577,682,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Genitalia (
<figureCitation id="1379FAE8FFA5F079FC8AFBA9FC9CFBF8" box="[813,893,1024,1050]" captionStart="Figures 98–102" captionStartId="57.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionText="Figures 98–102. Female genitalia of Chlamydastis. 98) C. colleenhitchcockae, paratype, 99-SRNP-17199. 99) C. bernardoespinozai, paratype, 07-SRNP-40851. 100) C. bobandersoni, paratype, INBIOCRI00206262590. 101) C. carlosviquezi, paratype, 07-SRNP-40632. 102) C. christerhanssoni, paratype, 07-SRNP-40631." pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Fig. 99</figureCitation>
) with papillae anales slender, slightly converging posteriorly; ductus bursae with complex sclerotization in anterior 0.6; signum large, paired lip-shaped, with an uninterrupted line of sclerotization between its two lateral projections.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFDE66DFFA5F079FF67FBC4FA7DFB48" blockId="19.[192,1440,1133,1194]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FF67FBC4FE93FB6A" bold="true" box="[192,370,1133,1160]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">DNA barcodes.</emphasis>
The 19 barcode sequences of 
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FD18FBC7FC46FB65" authorityName="Phillips and Brown" authorityYear="2021" box="[703,935,1133,1160]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Chlamydastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernardoespinozai">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FD18FBC7FC46FB65" box="[703,935,1133,1160]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">C. bernardoespinozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
form a BIN (BOLD:AAA1074) with an average distance of 0.13% among the sequences, and a distance of 4.17% to its nearest neighbor, 
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FB18FB39FA77FB4B" authorityName="Phillips and Brown" authorityYear="2021" box="[1215,1430,1167,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Chlamydastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marianofigueresi">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FB18FB39FA77FB4B" box="[1215,1430,1167,1194]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">C. marianofigueresi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358B5E6FFA5F079FF67FB10FD96FB17" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BFDE66DFFA5F079FF67FB10FD96FB17" blockId="19.[191,1440,1209,1269]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FF67FB10FEBBFB31" bold="true" box="[192,346,1209,1235]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FEC7FB10FD23FB31" authorityName="Phillips and Brown" authorityYear="2021" box="[352,706,1209,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Chlamydastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernardoespinozai">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FEC7FB10FD23FB31" box="[352,706,1209,1235]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Chlamydastis bernardoespinozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been collected from 
<quantity id="4CBA4B88FFA5F079FC73FB10FB82FB36" box="[980,1123,1209,1236]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" unit="m" value="450.0" valueMax="700.0" valueMin="200.0">200 to 700 m</quantity>
on both slopes of the central cordillera and in the rainforest of ACG.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358B5E6FFA5F079FF67FAADFABAFA4C" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BFDE66DFFA5F079FF67FAADFAEBFAA2" blockId="19.[192,1441,1284,1345]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FF67FAADFEC1FAFC" bold="true" box="[192,288,1284,1310]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Biology.</emphasis>
This species has been reared from larvae feeding on 
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FCD9FAACFB97FAFC" box="[894,1142,1285,1311]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" genus="Chrysophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cainito">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FCD9FAACFB97FAFC" box="[894,1142,1285,1311]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Chrysophyllum cainito</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. (n = 3), 
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FB5CFAACFE6AFAA2" authority="Cronquist" authorityName="Cronquist" authorityYear="1945" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" genus="Chrysophyllum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brenesii">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FB5CFAACFEF5FAA2" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Chrysophyllum brenesii</emphasis>
Cronquist
</taxonomicName>
(n = 8), and 
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FDBBFA8EFC52FAA2" authority="(Standl.) Baehni" authorityName="Baehni" authorityYear="1942" baseAuthorityName="Standl." box="[540,947,1318,1345]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" genus="Pouteria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="izabalensis">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FDBBFA8EFD16FAA2" box="[540,759,1318,1344]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pouteria izabalensis</emphasis>
(Standl.) Baehni
</taxonomicName>
(n = 1) (
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FBB4FA8FFB72FAA2" box="[1043,1171,1318,1344]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapotaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Sapotaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<tableCitation id="C6C0D3D6FFA5F079FB0FFA8FFB1BFAA2" box="[1192,1274,1318,1344]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="8.[192,255,214,240]" captionText="Table 1. Chlamydastis from Costa Rica. Food plant summary. Number (n) of rearing records for each plant species and family." pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFDE66DFFA5F079FF67FAF9FABAFA4C" blockId="19.[192,1440,1360,1454]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FF67FAF9FE63FA88" bold="true" box="[192,386,1360,1386]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Immature stages</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="1379FAE8FFA5F079FE37FAF9FE0FFA89" box="[400,494,1360,1387]" captionStart="Figures 124–129" captionStartId="61.[192,279,1296,1322]" captionTargetBox="[192,1440,213,1266]" captionTargetId="figure-46@61.[192,1440,213,1267]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="Figures 124–129. Chlamydastis immature stages. 124) C. vividella, 09-SRNP-1964. 125) C. bernardoespinozai, 09-SRNP-114.126) Cocoon of C. marianofigueresi, 08-SRNP-36402. 127) C. carlosviquezi, 07-SRNP-40631. 128) C. christhompsoni, 09-SRNP-71014. 129) C. elenaulateae, 09-SRNP-2109." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042083" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5042083/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Fig. 125</figureCitation>
). Head amber; prothorax (T1) gray with a pair of fused black pinacula on shield; T2– T3 with a pair of small, rounded, lateral protuberances (smaller in T3), black with two longitudinal white lines; abdominal segments pale green with small, lateral, translucent pale beige protuberances; A10 pale orange.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C358B5E6FFA5F079FF67FA17FEA0F9F9" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BFDE66DFFA5F079FF67FA17FEA0F9F9" blockId="19.[192,1440,1469,1563]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FF67FA17FEA7FA3A" bold="true" box="[192,326,1470,1496]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Etymology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C429DEEFFA5F079FEEBFA14FD52FA35" authorityName="Phillips and Brown" authorityYear="2021" box="[332,691,1469,1495]" class="Insecta" family="Oecophoridae" genus="Chlamydastis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernardoespinozai">
<emphasis id="B9363A7FFFA5F079FEEBFA14FD52FA35" box="[332,691,1469,1495]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Chlamydastis bernardoespinozai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named for our Costa Rican friend and colleague Bernardo Espinoza in recognition of his curatorial and taxonomic contributions to the national biodiversity inventory of 
<collectingCountry id="F355A6FDFFA5F079FF67F9A8FEDCF9F9" box="[192,317,1537,1563]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
